The simple reaction mechanisms in an acidic electrolyte are favorable to fast reaction kinetics [8, 9]. However, the corrosive nature of the acidic environment significantly limits active and stable catalysts to noble-metal-based materials, which increases costs and hinders the large-scale application of water electrolysis [10, 11]. In neutral and alkaline electrolytes, due to the lack of H+, the Volmer step becomes:4∗+H2O+e-→∗H+OH-\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
