Electrochemical measurements were performed on a Gamry Reference 600 electrochemical workstation. Experiments were conducted using a three-electrode configuration with a prepared sample (~ 0.5 cm2), a graphite electrode, and a Hg/HgO electrode serving as the working, counter, and reference electrodes, respectively. Cyclic voltammetry (CV) was measured at a scan rate of 2 mV s−1 with iR compensation [current-interrupt (CI) mode]. Potentials of the reference electrode were converted to the reversible hydrogen electrode (RHE) using the following equation:7ERHE=EHg/HgO+0.098+0.0591×pH\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
